09/10/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- US Ambassador to Kosovo Christopher Dell confirmed on Thursday (October 8th) that his country will help monitor the November 15th municipal elections. At the same time, Dell said Kosovo must overcome the need for international monitoring, a crucial test of democracy. 
On Wednesday, the European Commission (EC) announced it will monitor the elections, at the request of the Kosovo government. Prime Minister Hashim Thaci welcomed the EC's decision, saying it will strengthen the credibility of the elections process. (Kosova Sot, Express, Koha Ditore - 09/10/09; Kohavision, TV 21 - 08/10/09)
